                        Silius Italicus of the warres betwene Annibal, and Scipio in Latin uerse: much like Lucan of the warres betwene Pompey, and Caesar. 
                        But giue mee still Liuie of the one, and Caesar himself of the other: in comparison of whome Silius, and Lucan ar but trifles. No other
                        warres in the world , comparable to theise twoe. (The next, the terrible warres betwene Sylla, and Marius: who tawgt Caesar his lesson:
                        brauely also displayed in Latin verses bie three of M. Smythes, and mie gallant poets. of Homers and Uirgils wing.
                    </marginalia_text>
